  "text": "Similar results were obtained by Farnik et al. [CITATION_1] who used age-and sex-matched HCV infected patients as the control group in their study of vitamin D in patients with chronic hepatitis B. They also reported that in patients with chronic hepatitis C, the mean vitamin D level, although still low (18.15 ng/ml), was higher than in patients infected with HBV. Again, the difference was not statistically significant.",
